getShortTermChange(
  x,
  assay.type = "counts",
  rarefy = FALSE,
  compositional = FALSE,
  depth = min(assay(x, assay.type)),
  ...
)

Arguments

x

a SummarizedExperiment object.

assay.type

Character scalar. Specifies the name of assay used in calculation. (Default: "counts")

rarefy

Logical scalar. Whether to rarefy counts. (Default: FALSE)

compositional

Logical scalar. Whether to transform counts. (Default: FALSE)

depth

Integer scalar. Specifies the depth used in rarefying. (Default: min(assay(x, assay.type)))

...

additional arguments.

Value

dataframe with short term change calculations.

Details

This approach is used by Wisnoski NI and colleagues https://github.com/nwisnoski/ul-seedbank. Their approach is based on the following calculation log(present abundance/past abundance). Also a compositional version using relative abundance similar to Brian WJi, Sheth R et al https://www.nature.com/articles/s41564-020-0685-1 can be used. This approach is useful for identifying short term growth behaviors of taxa.
